cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.NI. 

This paper deals with information theory and communication, specifically the capacity of a channel with input constraints and feedback. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves coding theory and algorithms, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of dynamic programming and optimization techniques could also place the paper in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with communication networks, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
